        {
          "type": "multipleChoice",
          "question": "To make a promise, use 'will' like in the sentence 'I will always be your friend.' For offers, say something like 'I will give you a ride home.' When making a bet, you might say, 'I will bet $5 on that game.' For challenges, you could say, 'I will race you to the end of the street.' 2) Why do we use will? Make one choice below.",
          "options": ["promises", "offers", "impulsive bets", "challenges", "all these beside right", "hour"],
          "correctAnswer": "all these beside right" 
        },
